♪♪

08:50.665 --> 08:53.466
There's a spot
in San Ysidro off Exit 29.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.268
Should be
about an hour away.

08:55.336 --> 08:56.669
What about Chadwick?

08:56.737 --> 08:58.604
Well, if things go right,

08:58.673 --> 09:00.806
the shooting shouldn't
be tied to us or the bar.

09:00.875 --> 09:03.409
Then we tell Chadwick
we don't need him anymore.

09:06.547 --> 09:10.549
There's no upside
in offing a cop, Pope.

09:10.618 --> 09:13.952
Sometimes things
have to be done.

09:14.021 --> 09:15.954
Doesn't matter
who it is.

09:16.023 --> 09:20.759
♪♪

09:20.828 --> 09:23.496
Chadwick's the only one
who knows anything, man.

09:23.564 --> 09:26.766
He talks, he'd be
hanging himself.

09:28.836 --> 09:31.436
The guy's crazy.

09:31.438 --> 09:32.705
Who knows
what he's gonna say?

09:32.773 --> 09:34.639
The feds are onto him,
they're on to us.

09:34.641 --> 09:36.641
He's the one that went rogue
and shot the dude.

09:36.643 --> 09:37.910
J and Pope get this done,

09:37.979 --> 09:40.045
and Chadwick walks as long
as he keeps his mouth shut.

09:40.047 --> 09:41.380
Yeah, we'll see
if J's plan works.

09:41.448 --> 09:43.849
J's plan is gonna work,
man, okay?

09:43.851 --> 09:44.917
So just relax.
Don't tell me to relax, okay?

09:44.986 --> 09:46.519
I'm the one tied
to all this shit.

09:46.587 --> 09:48.120
We were all there, man, alright?
All of us.

09:48.189 --> 09:50.189
It wasn't just you.
Yeah, Livengood
would still be alive

09:50.257 --> 09:51.656
if it weren't for me.
We are a family,
and we'll stick together,

09:51.658 --> 09:53.860
so get that shit
out of your head.

09:55.997 --> 09:57.597
God damn it.

10:12.347 --> 10:14.046
[ Engine shuts off ]

10:18.085 --> 10:20.085
Any trouble
crossing the border?

10:20.154 --> 10:21.220
No.

10:21.288 --> 10:22.955
You got the money?

10:27.294 --> 10:29.094
You have his car, too?

10:29.163 --> 10:30.429
It's in there.

10:30.497 --> 10:32.565
He's in the trunk.

10:32.633 --> 10:35.968
Give me the keys.
Both vehicles.

10:36.037 --> 10:37.636
We need to make it
look drug-related,

10:37.705 --> 10:39.172
uh, something
on the border.

10:39.240 --> 10:42.542
Street gang, cartel-affiliated,
that kind of thing.

10:44.712 --> 10:46.379
Like a deal gone bad?

10:46.447 --> 10:49.181
More like a hit.

10:49.250 --> 10:50.183
So who is it?

10:50.251 --> 10:52.184
Does that matter?

10:52.253 --> 10:54.253
Yes.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.189
He's DEA.

10:56.257 --> 10:58.257
[ Scoffs ] Adiós.

10:58.325 --> 10:59.858
No, no, no. Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait, wait.

10:59.927 --> 11:02.061
Hold up.
Hey.

11:02.129 --> 11:04.063
Nobody you do business with
wants 10 grand?

11:04.131 --> 11:06.399
Nobody wants that kind
of attention.

11:06.467 --> 11:07.800
How about 20 grand?

11:07.868 --> 11:10.535
Nobody?
You sure about this?

11:10.537 --> 11:12.205
Come on.

11:12.273 --> 11:13.940
What's it gonna take?

11:16.343 --> 11:18.611
25.

11:18.679 --> 11:21.080
And you're gonna have
a lot more driving to do.

11:21.148 --> 11:24.483
There's a house in Otay Mesa
on this side of the border.

11:24.551 --> 11:26.619
That's where
they'll meet you.

11:31.058 --> 11:33.058
Linda:
Thanks for meeting me.

11:33.127 --> 11:36.262
Yeah, well, it's nice.
They like to play together.

11:37.665 --> 11:40.065
Baz is obsessed
with those swings.

11:40.134 --> 11:41.266
Rah!

11:41.335 --> 11:43.002
Baz, Jesus Christ.

11:43.070 --> 11:44.604
You're gonna
break your neck.

11:44.672 --> 11:45.938
Come on.

11:46.007 --> 11:48.307
-Watch this, Baz.
-He's like a wild animal.

11:49.210 --> 11:51.743
Yeah.

11:51.813 --> 11:54.213
You got lucky
that Andrew's so calm.

12:07.629 --> 12:10.229
So, about Max.

12:10.298 --> 12:16.168
Uh, he comes in
around 4:00 most days.

12:16.237 --> 12:18.304
He'll have
a couple drinks,

12:18.372 --> 12:22.441
then he picks a girl
and he goes to the VIP room.

12:22.510 --> 12:25.311
You think you could get me
into one of those rooms?

12:25.379 --> 12:26.512
What do you mean?

12:26.580 --> 12:31.317
I mean have him come in,
let him have his drink,

12:31.385 --> 12:33.319
and then you just tell him
that Sinnamon or Jade

12:33.387 --> 12:35.187
or whoever is waiting for him
in the VIP room.
No.

12:35.256 --> 12:37.657
No, no,
he chooses who he wants.

12:37.725 --> 12:39.792
He'll like to be chosen.

12:43.264 --> 12:45.597
Look, it's $1,500
up front for you.

12:45.599 --> 12:49.669
No, I-I-I got a certain lane
that I try to stay in.

12:49.737 --> 12:50.936
You know what I mean?

12:51.005 --> 12:53.973
I'm just doing this
to protect my kids.

12:55.877 --> 12:58.944
That's all.
Same as anyone would do.

12:59.013 --> 13:01.613
[ Sighs ]

13:01.683 --> 13:11.023
♪♪

13:13.627 --> 13:15.294
[ Sniffs ]

13:20.834 --> 13:22.768
What's up?

13:22.836 --> 13:25.037
Ah, J and Pope
still not back?

13:25.039 --> 13:28.440
They called last night.
It's gonna take a little longer.

13:28.442 --> 13:30.042
What are you doing here?

13:30.111 --> 13:33.845
[ Gate buzzer ringing ]

13:33.915 --> 13:35.847
Who's that?
[ Beep ]

13:35.917 --> 13:37.583
[ Phone thuds ]
Is that Frankie?

13:37.651 --> 13:40.652
Yeah, I told her to come by.
She found a hawala.

13:40.722 --> 13:42.654
I figured you might
want to hear.

13:42.724 --> 13:45.257
It's gotta be today?

13:45.326 --> 13:47.059
Hey, man, if you
wanna sit around

13:47.128 --> 13:50.596
and worry about shit
that we can't control, go ahead.

13:50.664 --> 13:53.132
But I'm gonna try to bring
some more work in.

13:55.403 --> 13:57.069
Morning.

13:59.873 --> 14:01.340
Bad time?

14:01.409 --> 14:04.009
No.
What's up?

14:04.078 --> 14:05.677
I got a guy.

14:05.747 --> 14:08.680
Does money transfers for big
players from here to L.A.

14:08.750 --> 14:10.482
Up to $250,000
each transaction.

14:10.551 --> 14:12.884
Well, he's probably sitting
on a lot more than that.

14:12.886 --> 14:13.953
How much more?

14:14.021 --> 14:15.821
At least four
or five times that.

14:15.889 --> 14:18.157
These guys take money in
and they give it out.

14:18.225 --> 14:21.493
If he can move a quarter
of a million on any given day,

14:21.495 --> 14:23.495
he's gotta be keeping
more than that somewhere.

14:23.564 --> 14:27.032
Yeah, a safe, building, truck.
Something.

14:27.101 --> 14:28.500
Be like robbing a bank.

14:28.569 --> 14:31.637
Man, we just gotta find out
where his bank is.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.239
If you want to find out
where he keeps his,

14:33.307 --> 14:35.240
I can meet with him
today.

14:35.309 --> 14:37.109
We can check out the location.
You can follow me.

14:37.178 --> 14:39.578
Today's not gonna work.

14:39.647 --> 14:41.513
[ Scoffs ]
Okay, when?

14:41.582 --> 14:43.216
We'll give you a call.

14:46.920 --> 14:49.922
Hey, I'll talk to him.

14:51.125 --> 14:53.192
I need this, too.

14:53.260 --> 14:54.860
The sooner the better.

14:54.928 --> 15:01.933
♪♪

15:01.935 --> 15:08.941
♪♪

15:09.010 --> 15:16.148
♪♪

15:16.150 --> 15:18.083
[ Engine shuts off ]

15:18.152 --> 15:20.352
I guess this is it.

15:20.421 --> 15:22.221
Uh-huh.

15:22.290 --> 15:24.290
Anybody looking
for our guy yet?

15:26.694 --> 15:28.394
No, we're good.

15:31.965 --> 15:33.299
[ Thud ]

15:39.973 --> 15:44.844
♪♪

15:44.912 --> 15:46.646
Alright, let's do this.

15:46.714 --> 15:53.919
♪♪

15:53.988 --> 16:01.527
♪♪

16:01.595 --> 16:03.062
The doctor sent you?

16:03.130 --> 16:05.931
No.
<i> Dios me envio.</i>

16:06.000 --> 16:08.367
<i> Claro.</i>
<i> Doctor.</i>

16:09.937 --> 16:11.937
<i> Donde esta el?</i>

16:12.006 --> 16:13.406
In the back.

16:15.476 --> 16:17.409
[ Speaks Spanish ]

16:17.478 --> 16:19.278
He wants us to get it.

16:23.150 --> 16:25.217
Look, I'm not gonna come
looking for you, Renn, okay?

16:25.219 --> 16:27.619
I just want to know
where you are. That's all.

16:27.621 --> 16:29.088
Call me back.

16:29.156 --> 16:30.890
[ Cellphone beeps ]

16:37.765 --> 16:39.232
[ Door closes ]

16:43.104 --> 16:45.037
Hey, if you don't wanna
check out this hawala,

16:45.039 --> 16:46.305
I will.

16:46.374 --> 16:48.840
I can't just stew in this shit
all day, man, okay?

16:48.842 --> 16:50.242
I'm in.

16:50.311 --> 16:52.078
What?

16:54.648 --> 16:56.916
I'm in.

16:56.984 --> 16:58.651
Alright.

17:00.588 --> 17:02.454
You know, if this shit
with Livengood goes sideways,

17:02.523 --> 17:04.056
I think it'd be smart
to have some cash

17:04.125 --> 17:05.791
to get the hell
out of here.

17:05.859 --> 17:07.527
Alright.

17:07.595 --> 17:08.928
Let's do it.

17:08.996 --> 17:10.796
Figure out the location
of Frankie's meet.

17:10.864 --> 17:13.065
If it looks like a place
where they'd be holding
the bank, then we hit it.

17:13.067 --> 17:14.866
Alright, well, how do we find
the bank in the building?

17:14.936 --> 17:16.335
Tracking device.

17:16.404 --> 17:18.137
Put it in the cash that Frankie
gives them to launder.

17:18.206 --> 17:20.672
If they hear a beeping
transmitter in the stack,

17:20.742 --> 17:23.475
we're burned.

17:23.477 --> 17:24.810
I know.

17:24.878 --> 17:26.345
Give her a call.

17:28.482 --> 17:29.881
Let's do this.

17:29.951 --> 17:31.551
Alright.

17:36.023 --> 17:37.256
<i> Su mano.</i>

17:39.493 --> 17:40.292
What?

17:40.294 --> 17:42.061
<i> Cortarlo la mano.</i>

17:42.764 --> 17:44.330
[ Speaks Spanish ]

17:46.367 --> 17:48.768
They want us to cut
off his hand.

17:48.836 --> 17:50.770
Okay. Why?

17:50.838 --> 17:53.906
Must be a calling card.

17:53.975 --> 17:55.575
Sells the story.

17:57.378 --> 17:59.145
Well, you better
get on it.

18:02.650 --> 18:04.049
[ Sighs ]

18:04.118 --> 18:11.457
♪♪

18:11.525 --> 18:18.464
♪♪

18:18.532 --> 18:25.671
♪♪

18:25.739 --> 18:27.406
[ Grunts ]

18:27.475 --> 18:28.941
[ Crack ]

18:29.010 --> 18:30.542
[ Grunts ]

18:30.612 --> 18:37.950
♪♪

18:38.019 --> 18:40.219
What about the car?

18:40.288 --> 18:42.622
Seven miles further
down the road.

18:42.690 --> 18:45.157
You'll be crossing
into Indian lands.

18:45.159 --> 18:47.827
Leave his car on the side.

18:47.895 --> 18:49.695
Hand on
the passenger seat.

18:49.763 --> 18:50.630
Why there?

18:50.698 --> 18:53.499
Well, they have
their own police, right?

18:53.567 --> 18:56.235
No DEA or FBI
without their permission.

18:56.304 --> 18:58.638
Their police will find it
when we tell 'em to.

18:58.706 --> 19:05.177
♪♪

19:05.246 --> 19:08.047
[ Speaks Spanish ]

19:08.115 --> 19:16.121
♪♪

19:16.190 --> 19:24.063
♪♪

19:24.131 --> 19:31.937
♪♪

19:32.006 --> 19:34.606
<i> Uno, dos, tres.</i>

19:34.608 --> 19:40.946
♪♪

19:41.015 --> 19:47.553
♪♪

19:47.621 --> 19:50.022
I guess they're gonna drag him
under the border.

19:50.091 --> 19:58.698
♪♪

19:58.766 --> 20:07.273
♪♪

20:13.581 --> 20:15.515
Meeting's this afternoon.

20:15.583 --> 20:18.050
That's as late
as I could get.

20:18.052 --> 20:19.184
Where's the location?

20:19.253 --> 20:23.455
10th and Mesa --
two-story building.

20:23.457 --> 20:25.124
How much you thinking
about sending?

20:25.192 --> 20:26.592
$30,000.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.994
I worked it out with a friend
I trust in Costa Rica.

20:29.063 --> 20:30.296
You have that?

20:31.933 --> 20:34.533
We need to talk about
something first.

20:34.602 --> 20:35.935
We'll figure out
a finder's fee.

20:36.003 --> 20:37.537
No.

20:37.605 --> 20:39.739
No fee.

20:39.807 --> 20:43.008
I need to be cut in.

20:43.077 --> 20:45.010
How much?

20:45.079 --> 20:46.746
Half.

20:49.617 --> 20:51.951
You know we're talking about
a million dollars in cash,

20:52.019 --> 20:53.619
maybe even more, right?

20:53.687 --> 20:55.287
This guy gets robbed,

20:55.356 --> 20:57.489
he's gonna start looking
at new faces, mine first.

20:57.558 --> 21:00.760
When that bridge burns,
I need to be gone.

21:00.828 --> 21:02.094
For good.

21:02.163 --> 21:04.764
The $30,000's damn near
all the money I have.

21:04.832 --> 21:07.767
If the exchange goes bad,
I get caught,

21:07.835 --> 21:08.834
I'm out all my money.

21:08.903 --> 21:10.169
It's a lot of risk.

21:10.237 --> 21:13.238
We're risking our asses
actually doing the job.

21:13.307 --> 21:16.642
Last I heard,
prison isn't that great.

21:16.710 --> 21:20.512
Fair compensation.
That's all I'm asking for.

21:20.581 --> 21:21.647
Okay.

21:24.185 --> 21:27.853
Alright, we'll, uh,
split it up equally.

21:27.922 --> 21:29.388
How many?

21:29.457 --> 21:31.123
With you, five.

21:31.125 --> 21:39.932
♪♪

21:42.470 --> 21:44.203
[ Engine shuts off ]

21:44.271 --> 21:46.405
[ "Edge of Seventeen" playing ]

21:49.943 --> 21:51.310
[ Knock on door ]

21:54.148 --> 21:57.683
♪ And a melody

21:57.751 --> 21:59.886
♪ Nothin' else mattered

22:02.089 --> 22:04.690
♪ Just like
the white winged dove ♪

22:04.758 --> 22:07.226
♪ Sings a song,
sounds like she's singin' ♪

22:07.295 --> 22:10.696
♪ Ooh, baby, ooh, said ooh

22:10.764 --> 22:13.098
♪ Just like
the white winged dove ♪

22:13.167 --> 22:15.635
♪ Sings a song,
sounds like she's singin' ♪

22:15.703 --> 22:19.505
♪ Said ooh, baby, ooh,
said ooh ♪

22:19.573 --> 22:23.442
♪ The clouds never expect it

22:23.511 --> 22:25.511
♪ When it rains

22:25.579 --> 22:27.780
♪ But the sea

22:34.121 --> 22:35.655
♪ Ever want something so bad

22:35.723 --> 22:37.390
♪ You could taste it?

22:39.593 --> 22:42.662
♪ Made the deadline
and you passed the test ♪

22:42.730 --> 22:46.465
♪ Sabotage seems safer
than success ♪

22:46.534 --> 22:48.934
♪ Put it off until tomorrow

22:49.003 --> 22:52.137
♪ I've heard it all before

22:52.206 --> 22:56.008
♪ But it's one on one

22:56.010 --> 22:59.144
♪ One on one

22:59.213 --> 23:01.813
♪ It's you and me
against the world ♪

23:01.883 --> 23:04.116
♪ It's one on one

23:06.020 --> 23:09.355
♪ I need some time to think
the whole thing over ♪

23:09.423 --> 23:12.758
♪ You say you want
to save the world alone ♪

23:12.826 --> 23:15.827
♪ I want to taste and test
the waters with you ♪

23:15.897 --> 23:21.367
♪ It's not so easy
when you're on you own ♪

23:21.435 --> 23:30.175
♪♪

23:30.244 --> 23:32.378
-You ready, baby?
-Yeah.

23:32.446 --> 23:34.980
-Let's have some real fun.
-Mm-hmm. You know it.

23:35.049 --> 23:36.315
Yeah.

23:36.384 --> 23:38.584
♪ No excuses,
I just want the truth ♪

23:38.652 --> 23:39.851
Shit.

23:39.853 --> 23:41.987
♪ Reputation
is a fragile thing ♪

23:42.056 --> 23:45.257
♪ I know you know it

23:45.259 --> 23:49.261
♪ Well, it's one on one

23:49.330 --> 23:52.331
♪ One on one

23:52.400 --> 23:55.000
♪ It's you and me
against the world ♪

23:55.069 --> 23:56.135
♪ It's one on...

24:03.344 --> 24:08.213
Everything I've got,
down to what can fit in a purse.

24:08.282 --> 24:13.085
And you're gonna give it
to some rando in Costa Rica?

24:13.087 --> 24:15.220
He's not a rando.

24:15.289 --> 24:17.156
You're really gonna stay
down there?

24:17.224 --> 24:20.559
Dollar goes far in that part
of the world.

24:20.628 --> 24:23.763
You'll get bored,
come back.

24:23.831 --> 24:25.697
No, I'm done.

24:25.767 --> 24:29.535
I was looking for a way out,
and then you showed up.

24:36.043 --> 24:44.916
♪♪

24:44.918 --> 24:53.659
♪♪

24:53.727 --> 24:55.661
[ Sighs ]

24:57.398 --> 25:00.399
Better safe, right?

25:00.468 --> 25:01.601
Yeah.

25:01.669 --> 25:05.938
♪♪

25:06.007 --> 25:07.739
[ Cellphone chiming ]

25:07.741 --> 25:12.812
♪♪

25:12.880 --> 25:14.079
It's his daughter.

25:14.148 --> 25:16.348
He's supposed to be picking her
up from soccer practice.

25:16.350 --> 25:17.883
He's late.

25:17.951 --> 25:25.891
♪♪

25:25.959 --> 25:33.965
♪♪

25:33.967 --> 25:41.973
♪♪

25:41.975 --> 25:49.981
♪♪

25:49.983 --> 25:52.351
[ Rock music playing ]

25:56.257 --> 25:58.390
Is that the thing people use
to find their wallets?

25:58.392 --> 26:03.462
Uh, this is, yeah,
but this is LBS.

26:03.531 --> 26:05.665
GPS can locate
a building,

26:05.733 --> 26:09.001
but if you want to know
what room inside that building,

26:09.003 --> 26:13.739
the LBS can pinpoint
a location within 40 feet.

26:13.807 --> 26:16.676
Here I was thinking
that J's the tech nerd.

26:16.744 --> 26:19.879
I have a regular
that comes into my bar

26:19.947 --> 26:23.282
MacGyvering this kind of shit
all the time.

26:23.351 --> 26:24.884
Sent me a couple
YouTube clips,

26:24.952 --> 26:29.589
and I figured
the rest out on my own.

26:32.026 --> 26:33.559
Where's Frankie?

26:33.627 --> 26:36.095
Oh, she'll be back.
She's just getting changed.

26:36.163 --> 26:37.763
Changed?

26:37.831 --> 26:40.432
Why's she
getting changed?

26:40.434 --> 26:42.902
Yeah, I don't know, man.
It's what she does.

26:46.908 --> 26:50.510
You know, she's really
gonna go and do that
Central America thing.

26:51.845 --> 26:54.179
Yeah, well,
could be us one day.

26:54.248 --> 26:55.915
Hey, you heard
from them?

26:58.252 --> 26:59.485
No.

27:02.189 --> 27:06.325
You know, it's kind of our fault
what happened to Frankie.

27:06.394 --> 27:08.194
With what Smurf did
and all.

27:11.332 --> 27:14.200
I tell you what,
we're definitely giving her

27:14.268 --> 27:16.268
one hell
of a going-away present.

27:16.337 --> 27:24.210
♪♪

27:24.278 --> 27:25.745
Boom.

27:25.813 --> 27:32.684
♪♪

27:32.754 --> 27:35.221
Not bad, man.

27:35.289 --> 27:37.623
Not bad?
It's a goddamn work of art.

27:37.691 --> 27:40.092
[<i> Up-tempo music playing</i> ]

27:40.094 --> 27:42.295
[ Indistinct talking ]

27:46.234 --> 27:48.033
Thanks, baby.

27:48.102 --> 27:49.234
Come see me again.

27:49.303 --> 27:51.036
Any time.

27:51.105 --> 27:54.106
♪ And in his mind

27:54.175 --> 27:56.175
♪ Sunglasses blind

27:56.243 --> 27:58.778
♪ Losing track of time

27:58.846 --> 28:01.713
♪ Pulling up to the home

28:01.783 --> 28:04.583
♪ Rolling up a smoke

28:04.652 --> 28:05.985
♪ He's left there alone

28:06.053 --> 28:07.386
Where's Linda?

28:07.455 --> 28:10.456
I just saw her leaving
when I was coming in.

28:10.524 --> 28:11.958
[ Door opens ]

28:14.128 --> 28:16.728
Hey!

28:16.798 --> 28:18.330
Hey!

28:18.332 --> 28:20.065
What the hell?

28:20.134 --> 28:22.401
You said
he was gonna be here.
He was. He left.

28:22.470 --> 28:23.803
You stole money from me.
You understand that?

28:23.871 --> 28:25.137
I did what you asked me
to do, Janine,

28:25.206 --> 28:27.339
but he -- he --
he knew something was up.

28:27.341 --> 28:28.740
What did you tell him?

28:28.810 --> 28:32.378
Look, I got kids
to protect, too.

28:34.148 --> 28:36.148
What did you tell him?

28:36.150 --> 28:39.218
♪♪

28:39.287 --> 28:41.153
[ Turn signal clicking ]

28:41.222 --> 28:50.630
♪♪

28:50.698 --> 28:53.098
Jesus.
What is this place?

28:53.167 --> 28:54.766
Teamsters?

28:54.836 --> 28:56.902
Longshoreman.

28:56.970 --> 29:00.572
Buddy I used to hang with,
his dad got him in.

29:00.642 --> 29:02.374
This is the one with
the tracking device in it.

29:02.376 --> 29:03.976
It's tucked
inside the band.

29:07.448 --> 29:08.848
Should get plenty of intel
inside.

29:08.916 --> 29:12.784
You know, entrances, exits,
cameras, all that shit.

29:12.854 --> 29:17.256
Yeah, we'll check the outside
while you're in there.

29:17.325 --> 29:18.390
Okay.

29:18.459 --> 29:27.466
♪♪

29:27.535 --> 29:28.934
[ Beep ]

29:29.003 --> 29:38.077
♪♪

29:38.145 --> 29:47.419
♪♪

29:47.421 --> 29:48.688
Security.

29:48.756 --> 29:50.756
Yeah, if I had a million dollars
in a union hall,

29:50.824 --> 29:52.424
I'd have security, too.

29:52.493 --> 29:59.565
♪♪

29:59.633 --> 30:00.766
[ Lock clicks ]

30:03.437 --> 30:04.303
Welcome to Local 4904.

30:04.372 --> 30:06.772
You have an appointment?
Yes.

30:06.840 --> 30:08.040
Who you here to see?

30:08.042 --> 30:09.609
The wizard.

30:11.713 --> 30:13.513
Any weapons?

30:13.581 --> 30:15.314
No.

30:15.383 --> 30:17.983
Tryin' to be
respectful, Miss.

30:18.052 --> 30:21.253
I got hams for hands.

30:21.322 --> 30:22.988
Gotta leave that here.

30:23.057 --> 30:29.529
♪♪

30:29.597 --> 30:35.735
♪♪

30:35.803 --> 30:38.003
You're good.
I'll let him know you're here.

30:38.072 --> 30:39.739
Have a seat.

30:39.807 --> 30:41.607
Thanks.

30:41.675 --> 30:51.417
♪♪

30:51.485 --> 30:53.319
Yeah.
Sounds good.

30:55.022 --> 30:56.355
Pope and J are
on their way back.

30:56.424 --> 30:57.823
They just got to
dump the truck.

30:57.892 --> 30:59.291
Did it go well?

30:59.293 --> 31:01.627
I don't know.

31:01.695 --> 31:03.563
Yeah, she's not moving.
She's still at the front.

31:03.631 --> 31:06.432
I'm guessing the bank is
nowhere near the front door.

31:06.500 --> 31:13.905
♪♪

31:13.907 --> 31:20.980
♪♪

31:21.048 --> 31:22.882
Okay, he'll see you.

31:24.786 --> 31:26.919
Look, the freeway entrance
is only half a mile.

31:26.988 --> 31:28.454
Two, three turns max.

31:28.522 --> 31:30.256
We can be
out of here fast.

31:30.324 --> 31:32.324
I'm thinking we can make
a distraction up front.

31:32.393 --> 31:33.926
Get in through the back?
Tactical gear?

31:33.995 --> 31:35.861
Big guns.
Scare the shit out of them.

31:35.929 --> 31:38.397
We need to figure out
how big this safe is
we're talking about.

31:38.466 --> 31:41.133
We should prepare
for the worst.

31:41.135 --> 31:43.068
Bring equipment.

31:43.137 --> 31:45.805
I mean, hell, we could
hit this tomorrow, man.

31:45.873 --> 31:47.607
Shit.
She's on the move.

31:47.675 --> 31:48.674
I know.

31:48.742 --> 31:51.611
Old bald guy in the back
of a union hall.

31:51.679 --> 31:54.480
Security looks like they're
gonna let you into Altamont.

31:54.548 --> 31:57.349
I've learned not to judge a book
by its cover.

31:57.351 --> 31:58.884
I've learned not to judge
my clients.

31:58.953 --> 32:01.353
Keeps me in business.

32:01.355 --> 32:02.922
Sit.

32:05.693 --> 32:08.360
$30,000.
To Costa Rica.

32:08.362 --> 32:16.968
♪♪

32:16.970 --> 32:25.311
♪♪

32:25.379 --> 32:26.378
No offense.

32:26.447 --> 32:27.847
None taken.

32:27.915 --> 32:35.387
♪♪

32:35.456 --> 32:42.994
♪♪

32:42.996 --> 32:45.064
My Costa Rica guy's
in San Jose.

32:45.132 --> 32:46.732
Is that okay?
Yeah.

32:46.800 --> 32:49.935
♪♪

32:50.004 --> 32:51.304
Okay.

32:53.541 --> 32:56.075
Think of a password.
It can be anything.

32:56.143 --> 32:57.343
I share it with my guy.

32:57.411 --> 32:58.744
You share it
with your recipient.

32:58.812 --> 33:00.479
The code matches,
they pick up the money,

33:00.548 --> 33:02.315
minus my 5%.

33:06.087 --> 33:07.787
"Freedom."

33:09.957 --> 33:11.156
"Freedom" it is.

33:11.225 --> 33:12.424
How soon?

33:12.493 --> 33:16.228
Should be processed
later this evening.

33:16.297 --> 33:17.497
Excellent.

33:17.565 --> 33:19.899
The lads
will show you out.

33:19.967 --> 33:21.433
Thanks.

33:21.502 --> 33:26.906
♪♪

33:26.974 --> 33:29.375
Think maybe we should
pick up the pace a little?

33:29.443 --> 33:31.410
We're far enough away.

33:33.647 --> 33:35.581
You watch TV?

33:35.649 --> 33:37.783
Uh, no, not really.

33:37.851 --> 33:42.121
I watched a lot.
You know, when I was a kid.

33:42.189 --> 33:43.455
Nature shows mostly.

33:43.457 --> 33:45.324
They kind of
calmed me down.

33:47.395 --> 33:50.662
We were, uh...

33:50.664 --> 33:53.132
never really kids.

33:53.201 --> 33:54.867
Me and your mom.

33:58.672 --> 34:00.706
But you were.
For a while, anyway.

34:04.946 --> 34:07.713
You and me,
we're not the same, J.

34:09.883 --> 34:11.517
Not like that.

34:13.354 --> 34:15.087
[ Explosion ]

34:28.636 --> 34:31.070
[ Tires screeching ]

34:33.775 --> 34:38.578
♪♪

34:38.646 --> 34:41.614
Hey, look, everybody.
Mommy's home.

34:42.916 --> 34:44.584
I didn't want
to leave them.

34:44.652 --> 34:46.852
Oh, Bree, it's fine.

34:46.920 --> 34:50.189
Cousin Max always
shows up unannounced.

34:50.257 --> 34:51.257
Really, it's fine.

34:51.325 --> 34:52.992
Thank you, Bree.

34:56.197 --> 35:00.932
Janine, you want to
come inside and talk?

35:00.934 --> 35:02.334
Yeah.

35:02.336 --> 35:05.737
Yeah, let's --
let's talk.

35:05.807 --> 35:09.341
Uh, why don't you guys
play outside?

35:09.343 --> 35:10.409
No. No, no.

35:10.478 --> 35:13.579
I-I think
they should see this.

35:16.083 --> 35:17.349
No, Max.

35:17.351 --> 35:18.884
No.

35:18.953 --> 35:20.586
Yeah.

35:22.824 --> 35:25.891
Come on.
We're just gonna talk.

35:25.960 --> 35:27.627
Alright, let's --
let's go in.

35:27.695 --> 35:29.495
Let's watch some TV.

35:29.563 --> 35:35.301
♪♪

35:35.369 --> 35:38.037
Watch TV.
Sit down.

35:38.105 --> 35:40.172
Guys, sit down.

35:40.174 --> 35:41.440
Here.

35:41.509 --> 35:43.175
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

35:43.177 --> 35:45.044
[ Clears throat ]

35:45.112 --> 35:47.913
You want to try to tell me
why you were setting me up?

35:47.981 --> 35:49.882
I just wanted to talk.

35:51.653 --> 35:54.053
Lying is just gonna
make this worse.

35:54.121 --> 35:57.523
No, really, I-I-I've been
thinking about some stuff,

35:57.591 --> 35:58.924
you know,
high-level shit,

35:58.993 --> 36:02.994
and, um, I wanted
to talk about how --

36:02.996 --> 36:06.465
how we could make
some more money.

36:06.534 --> 36:08.133
Yeah?
Yeah.

36:08.202 --> 36:09.268
Me and you?

36:09.337 --> 36:10.802
Mm-hmm.

36:10.804 --> 36:12.404
Yeah, doll?

36:12.406 --> 36:13.805
Yeah.

36:13.807 --> 36:15.741
Isn't so tough, right?

36:15.809 --> 36:16.776
Yeah.

36:19.747 --> 36:21.947
Hey.
[ Gasps ]

36:22.016 --> 36:24.483
Lie to me again.
Don't do this
in front of my kids.

36:24.552 --> 36:27.353
Lie to me again. Come on.
One more's all I need.

36:27.421 --> 36:29.955
Come on.
[ Choking ]

36:30.024 --> 36:32.091
Listen.

36:32.159 --> 36:35.561
Gonna kill me?
Is that what you were gonna do?

36:35.629 --> 36:37.162
Huh?

36:37.231 --> 36:39.631
Gonna try to kill me?

36:39.701 --> 36:41.633
How's that feel?

36:41.703 --> 36:43.402
What the hell is this?

36:44.105 --> 36:47.306
That was really
not smart.

36:47.375 --> 36:48.307
[ Gun clatters ]

36:48.376 --> 36:49.641
[ Gasping ]

36:49.711 --> 36:50.910
Want to see something?

36:50.978 --> 36:53.913
No.
Okay, not in front of my kids.

36:53.981 --> 36:54.980
Ah!

36:55.049 --> 36:57.884
Ow! Ow!
Ah!

37:00.187 --> 37:01.853
Ow!

37:01.855 --> 37:03.855
What'd you do that for?

37:03.925 --> 37:05.591
God, you little shit.

37:05.659 --> 37:08.127
[ Gunshot ]
Ah! Ah!

37:08.196 --> 37:10.596
Ah. Oh.

37:10.664 --> 37:12.598
You shot me?

37:12.666 --> 37:14.199
Ohh.

37:14.268 --> 37:15.534
Ow.

37:15.603 --> 37:17.269
Huh?

37:17.271 --> 37:19.271
[ Groans ]

37:19.273 --> 37:22.208
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:22.276 --> 37:23.943
God.

37:24.011 --> 37:26.145
Easy.

37:26.213 --> 37:27.479
Look away.

37:27.481 --> 37:30.015
[ Groans ]
You bi--

37:30.084 --> 37:31.217
[ Body thuds ]

37:31.285 --> 37:32.952
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:35.223 --> 37:37.623
Hey, come here.
[ Gun thuds ]

37:37.691 --> 37:40.593
Come here.
Come here.

37:43.030 --> 37:46.165
It's okay.
It's okay.

37:46.234 --> 37:47.499
Oh, God.

37:47.501 --> 37:48.900
It's okay.

37:48.902 --> 37:51.137
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:57.979 --> 37:59.044
Frankie: His office
was right about here.

37:59.113 --> 38:01.113
There was
an adjoining door.

38:01.182 --> 38:03.448
Craig: Were those two dudes
the only security at the door?

38:03.518 --> 38:05.184
Yeah, them and Wyatt
were the only three people

38:05.252 --> 38:06.719
in the building
as far as I could tell.

38:06.787 --> 38:08.387
Okay, so they only
do their business

38:08.455 --> 38:10.055
when the place is closed.

38:10.124 --> 38:11.123
Wyatt?

38:11.192 --> 38:12.925
I spotted his business card
on his desk.

38:12.994 --> 38:14.594
He's not very discreet.

38:16.397 --> 38:17.863
Alright, so,
we, uh,

38:17.865 --> 38:21.266
get to him first, then he can
bring us to the cash, yeah?

38:21.268 --> 38:23.869
Yeah, sounds good.
[ Clang ]

38:23.938 --> 38:25.938
Ah, the boys
are back from war.

38:28.676 --> 38:29.742
Frankie.

38:29.810 --> 38:32.277
We're into
the hawala thing.

38:32.279 --> 38:36.415
Frankie found us a big fish
not far from here.

38:36.483 --> 38:38.017
Good.

38:42.890 --> 38:45.424
Well, I should go home.

38:45.492 --> 38:47.059
We can finish up tomorrow.

38:56.704 --> 38:58.171
It's her contacts,
her cash.

38:58.239 --> 39:00.439
Figure she's in on the job
with us if that's alright.

39:00.507 --> 39:02.908
Yeah, all good.

39:02.910 --> 39:04.643
Livengood?

39:04.712 --> 39:09.048
We had to send the doc
an extra 15K, but it's handled.

39:09.116 --> 39:10.716
They just need
to find him now.

39:10.718 --> 39:20.325
♪♪

39:20.327 --> 39:22.061
[ Exhales deeply ]

39:24.799 --> 39:27.066
Alright, got these.

39:30.137 --> 39:31.804
You okay?

39:35.009 --> 39:39.344
I changed the license plate
to a dummy,

39:39.346 --> 39:41.947
put bullshit papers
in the glove compartment.

39:41.949 --> 39:45.084
We'll make sure
that nobody can find him.

39:45.152 --> 39:48.353
Did, uh, the neighbors
hear anything?

39:48.423 --> 39:51.556
Bree's the closest.
I'll talk to her.

39:51.558 --> 39:53.492
Alright.

39:53.560 --> 39:55.761
Let's go.

39:55.763 --> 39:58.497
I should come.

39:58.565 --> 40:00.099
Nah,
stay with your kids.

40:03.905 --> 40:06.705
Look,
it was self-defense.

40:06.774 --> 40:07.907
It's not like
you planned it.

40:07.975 --> 40:09.475
[ Car door closes ]

40:10.978 --> 40:12.945
I can come back.

40:15.650 --> 40:17.016
I'm fine.

40:18.986 --> 40:20.920
Okay.

40:20.988 --> 40:23.222
[ Engine starts ]

40:27.394 --> 40:29.595
Jesus Christ.

40:29.664 --> 40:36.401
♪♪

40:36.403 --> 40:42.675
♪♪

40:42.743 --> 40:44.543
And then she's gone?

40:44.612 --> 40:46.011
So she says.

40:46.013 --> 40:48.881
It's a big haul.
A million or so.

40:48.950 --> 40:50.883
Guy works out of
a union building.

40:50.952 --> 40:52.417
Not totally sure
where the cash is,

40:52.419 --> 40:53.886
but I figure
we all go back,

40:53.955 --> 40:56.155
take a look
before we finalize a plan.

40:56.223 --> 40:58.557
How do we find out
where the money is?

40:58.626 --> 41:00.693
I put a little mini
GPS tracking device

41:00.761 --> 41:02.427
in the cash
that Frankie gave him.

41:02.497 --> 41:04.497
[ Cellphone chimes ]

41:04.565 --> 41:06.499
Oh, shit.

41:06.567 --> 41:07.633
What?

41:07.702 --> 41:09.234
The money's not at
the union hall anymore.

41:09.304 --> 41:12.305
It's on the move.
What?

41:12.373 --> 41:15.040
Says it's about 10 miles
from here, but it's moving.

41:15.042 --> 41:17.776
Okay. Well, then wait
for it to land.

41:17.845 --> 41:19.444
No, no, we follow it.

41:19.446 --> 41:21.647
Find out how it's being moved
and where it's going.

41:21.716 --> 41:29.355
♪♪

41:44.939 --> 41:48.473
Andrew, hey, get ready

41:48.543 --> 41:52.912
for the best chili
you've ever had in 10 minutes.

41:57.952 --> 41:59.218
Are you okay?

42:02.423 --> 42:03.556
Here.

42:14.702 --> 42:16.602
That good, huh?

42:23.510 --> 42:25.044
[ Sighs ]

42:37.658 --> 42:40.426
Did you close your eyes
when I asked you to?

42:43.931 --> 42:45.598
Why not?

42:45.666 --> 42:47.500
You didn't
close yours.

42:50.938 --> 42:54.539
He was a bad man,
right?

42:54.609 --> 42:56.209
Yeah, baby.

42:59.614 --> 43:01.347
Yes, he was.

43:03.550 --> 43:06.285
You did good.

43:06.353 --> 43:07.987
Okay?

43:10.958 --> 43:12.625
Hey.

43:17.832 --> 43:19.532
[ Clatter ]

43:20.968 --> 43:23.002
Now, don't lose that.

43:28.643 --> 43:38.451
♪♪

43:38.519 --> 43:47.860
♪♪

43:47.929 --> 43:57.602
♪♪

43:57.604 --> 43:58.938
How far behind it
were we?

43:59.006 --> 44:00.873
About a mile.

44:00.942 --> 44:04.076
I think it turned
down another road.

44:04.145 --> 44:05.611
J: Is it still stopped?

44:05.680 --> 44:06.612
Yeah.

44:06.681 --> 44:13.152
♪♪

44:13.220 --> 44:15.888
It's been still
for a minute now.

44:15.957 --> 44:17.156
This way.

44:17.224 --> 44:24.363
♪♪

44:24.431 --> 44:31.504
♪♪

44:31.572 --> 44:38.711
♪♪

44:38.779 --> 44:40.079
Jesus.

44:44.185 --> 44:46.585
It's huge.

44:46.654 --> 44:49.188
Can you tell where the signal's
coming from?

44:49.256 --> 44:51.256
Yeah, south side
of the port.

44:51.258 --> 44:53.458
Dude's a longshoreman.

44:53.460 --> 44:55.060
Makes sense.
Secure.

44:55.129 --> 44:57.997
These places
are like Pendleton.

44:58.065 --> 44:59.198
Worse.

44:59.266 --> 45:01.600
It's easier
to break into Fort Knox.

45:01.669 --> 45:03.468
Tons of security
since 9/11.

45:03.470 --> 45:06.271
Yeah, Customs,
Coast Guard, cops.

45:06.341 --> 45:07.940
Deran:
Yeah, we'll figure it out.

45:08.009 --> 45:10.209
We make a plan,
and we follow it.

45:10.277 --> 45:12.411
That's what we do.
Right?

45:12.479 --> 45:18.417
♪♪

45:18.485 --> 45:20.419
Let's get to work.

45:20.487 --> 45:30.429
♪♪

45:30.497 --> 45:40.505
♪♪

45:40.575 --> 45:50.515
♪♪

45:50.585 --> 46:00.426
♪♪
